title: Salesforce Industries CPQ Developer Dump Questions
description: Ensuring web accessibility is vital for reaching a broader audience and creating inclusive digital experiences. This blog highlights essential web accessibility best practices, guidelines, and tools to make your websites accessible to everyone.
author: Wendy

body.raw:
Hi! Here are all the questions I collected in the process of getting Salesforce Industries CPQ certifications. Let's study with me. --- ## First 100 questions
1. What can a developer use to make sure a subscription ends at the end of the subscription plan?
a. An Effective From Date
b. A time policy
c. A time plan
d. An Effective Until Date
2. Which component uses a child catalog code to call the APIs and get a response with the appropriate products?
a. dcCatalog
b. dcChildCatalog
c. dcOfferList
3. Select all that apply: What are the phases of the Digital Commerce user experience model?
a. Configure
b. Basket
c. Cart
d. Payment
e. Submit
f. Checkout
4. Where do you go to populate the API cache? a. Catalogs b. Product Console c. Vlocity CMT Administration d. Setup
Ket qua:
c. Vlocity CMT Administration
5. How many times must you initialize the cache when working with cacheable APIs? a. Every time you modify your sales catalog b. Every time you modify a price entry c. The first time after you regenerate the cache d. The first time you begin using the cacheable APIs 6. Evaluation entity filters are used as "interal filters " for qualification entity filters. a. true b. false 7. For Product relationships, select a product in the Related Product field to modify attributes based on non-product-related factors. a. true b. false 8. A developer has updated the price of a product but still sees the previous price in the Digital Commerce API response. What job should the developer run to correct this issue? a. Regenerate Cached API records job b. Delete Expired API Cache job c. Migrate Cache Records job d. Populate API cache job. 9. How can a user understand changes to pricing applied in the cart? a. By clicking the Price Details icon on the line item b. The display text in the Products list in the cart c. Pricing adjustment do not display in the cart d. Popup message window after the order is submiited. 10. Which three ways can a developer filter the list of products when using the getCartsProducts method? (Choose 3) a. Using a product category b. Using a value that will be matched exactly to a value in a Product2 field # Result 1. d 2. c 3. abd 4. c 5. d 6. a 7. b 8. A 9. A
